sql:
SELECT administrative_area_level_2
FROM administrative_areas
WHERE administrative_area_level = 2;

SELECT administrative_area_level, SUM(population) AS total_population
FROM administrative_areas
GROUP BY administrative_area_level;

SELECT area_id, population
FROM administrative_areas
ORDER BY population DESC;

SELECT DISTINCT area_id
FROM administrative_areas
ORDER BY area_id;

external_knowledge:
"Latest population data" refers to the population data with the highest year; 
"Top 5 modes of transportation" refers to the 5 modes with the highest average mobility index in each area; 
"A user has read access" means the user can view data from a particular area; 
"Average mobility index" is a measure of how mobile people are in a particular area using a specific mode of transportation.

Note: This external knowledge is not required to understand the question, but it provides additional context.

- The mobility index is a measure of how easily people can move around an area; 
- A higher mobility index indicates better walkability; 
- The year 2023 is specified to focus on the most recent data available.
